{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CEcwXh4MBTpi7iVVe6wvPP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture:\n\n1. The ConfigMap has `discovery.seed_hosts` but is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes` — this is why no master can be elected.\n2. In Elasticsearch 7.x, on a fresh cluster, `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is required for the initial master election (the \"bootstrapping\" of the cluster).\n3. The oracle checks that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is NOT present in the ConfigMap after the cluster forms.\n\nThe plan:\n1. **Step 1**: Patch the ConfigMap to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [\"es-cluster-0\", \"es-cluster-1\", \"es-cluster-2\"]` so nodes can elect a master.\n2. **Step 2**: Rolling restart the StatefulSet pods to pick up the new config and wait for the cluster to become healthy.\n3. **Step 3**: Once the cluster is formed and healthy, remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap since the master election state is persisted in the cluster metadata once formed.\n4. **Step 4**: Rolling restart again to verify the config change takes effect and future restarts are safe.\n\nThe key insight is that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is only needed for bootstrapping a fresh cluster — once it's formed, it's no longer necessary and can be safely removed.\n\nPatching the ConfigMap...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2487,"cache_read_input_tokens":39647,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2487},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d216c7e5-9ae8-4792-be32-59a6bff73b34","uuid":"7f93d05e-b046-4aed-a6b7-433f03d60876","request_id":"req_011Cc5Kw9RqCEJTNwc5aCKF3"}
