{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LUPEw7kaPAP6a5ys6rCLL7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oracle passes. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The ConfigMap had `discovery.seed_hosts` (peers to connect to) but was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. In Elasticsearch 7.x, this setting is required for the very first master election on a fresh cluster — without it, every node waits forever for a master that can never be elected.\n\n**Fix (two-phase):**\n1. Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]` to the ConfigMap → rolling restart → cluster formed (green, 3 nodes, master elected).\n2. Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap → rolling restart → cluster stayed green. This is the critical cleanup: leaving the setting in place is dangerous because on subsequent restarts it can prevent nodes from rejoining an already-formed cluster (it signals \"ignore existing cluster state and form a new one\")."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":171,"cache_read_input_tokens":45343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":171},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d216c7e5-9ae8-4792-be32-59a6bff73b34","uuid":"a5bc4671-c004-41e6-b5ca-13a6dc42600c","request_id":"req_011Cc5LepSkCV354ACownhLV"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":604929,"duration_api_ms":80768,"ttft_ms":4203,"ttft_stream_ms":3290,"time_to_request_ms":37,"num_turns":20,"result":"Oracle passes. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The ConfigMap had `discovery.seed_hosts` (peers to connect to) but was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. In Elasticsearch 7.x, this setting is required for the very first master election on a fresh cluster — without it, every node waits forever for a master that can never be elected.\n\n**Fix (two-phase):**\n1. Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes: [es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2]` to the ConfigMap → rolling restart → cluster formed (green, 3 nodes, master elected).\n2. Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap → rolling restart → cluster stayed green. This is the critical cleanup: leaving the setting in place is dangerous because on subsequent restarts it can prevent nodes from rejoining an already-formed cluster (it signals \"ignore existing cluster state and form a new one\").","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d216c7e5-9ae8-4792-be32-59a6bff73b34","total_cost_usd":0.40181200000000006,"usage":{"input_tokens":17,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28844,"cache_read_input_tokens":586290,"output_tokens":3475,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28844,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":221,"cache_read_input_tokens":45343,"cache_creation_input_tokens":171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":171},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":605,"outputTokens":16,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.000685,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"clau